Choosing 'K' using K-fold cross validation¶

In [8]:
accuracy_rate = []
error_rate = []
# Will take some time
for i in range(1,40):
    knn = neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=i)
    score= cross_val_score(knn,df_scaled_features,df['whether he/she donated blood in March 2007'],cv=10)
    knn.fit(X_train,y_train)
    prediction_i = knn.predict(X_test)
    error_rate.append(np.mean(prediction_i != y_test))    
    accuracy_rate.append(score.mean())
In [9]:
fig, (ax1,ax2) = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(15,5))
fig.suptitle('Accuracy Rate vs Error Rate')
ax1.plot(range(1,40),accuracy_rate,color='blue')
ax2.plot(range(1,40),error_rate,color='red')
ax1.set(xlabel='K', ylabel='Accuracy Rate')
ax2.set(xlabel='K', ylabel='Error Rate')
fig.savefig('output-graph.png', dpi=500)

Creating a function to compare different KNN models¶

In [11]:
def knn_comparison(data, k):
    x = data[['Time (months)','Frequency (times)']].values
    y = data.iloc[:,-1].values
    clf = neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=k)
    clf.fit(x, y)
    # Plotting decision region
    plot_decision_regions(x, y, clf=clf, legend=2)
    # Adding axes annotations
    plt.xlabel('Time (months)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency (times)')
    plt.title('Knn with K='+ str(k))
    plt.show()

KNN Classifier Comparison on Blood Donation Dataset¶

Linear SVM for Linearly separable data¶

In [30]:
#Linear SVM
x = np.array(Data.drop(['whether he/she donated blood in March 2007'],1))
y = np.array(Data['whether he/she donated blood in March 2007'])
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x,y,test_size=0.33,random_state=3)

# The pipeline can be used as any other estimator and avoids leaking the test set into the train set
clf = make_pipeline(StandardScaler(),LinearSVC(random_state=1))
clf.fit(x_train,y_train)
y_pred=clf.predict(x_test)
accuracy=metrics.accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred)
print(accuracy)
print(classification_report(y_test,y_pred))
print(confusion_matrix(y_test,y_pred))
